Okay, Omi left this thing open... so I figure there shouldn't be a problem with me using it. Right? o.O;;;

Also... <lj-cut text="Meme-thing!">

<lj-embed id="1" />

Okay, I did a little research into Haruki's death. Finding information after the investigation has been closed isn't easy. At least I found out <i>why</i> it was just closed like that. Seems that there is more or less a blanket policy when someone that came out of Azure Hoshin is found dead. So I looked into that a little...

Damn, the statistics on this group isn't pretty. o.O;;;;

As far as I can tell? Only a handful of people that came out of that hell are <i>still</i> alive. A good number of THOSE are stuck in institutions. Considering how well Seiki reacted in the hospital, I'm betting on the fact that that isn't helping them much.

Okay. Tatsuki and I had his little <i>discussion</i>. Turns out that he really doesn't like me. He's also got some very impressive glares, they aren't up to clearing out a flower shop, but they are getting there. 

I was essentially ordered to stay away from you. Tatsuki didn't seem too pleased when I politely declined that order. There were a few other points on which we didn't seem to agree on... mainly the <i>me not dating you</i>. But, I understand that he's doing this because he's very protective about you; so I'm not holding anything of what was said against him. 

Unfortunately, I was given the impression that if he can figure out a way to force me to stop seeing you, he will do so. I'm going to be honest, I have several skeletons in my closet that I don't feel comfortable talking about. So please, don't ask. ^^;;; I'm not ashamed of anything that I've done (okay, maybe one or two, but that's beside the point), but I have to admit that there are things that when taken out of context will look <i>really</i> bad. -_-;;;
